                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> DONT WORRY, what you're experiencing is absolutely normal.<br /><br />CoB is the worst out of all our Lich series spells -yes, allure at its level is better than CoB-. I had the same problem on my mid levels: CoB is too harmfull and too poor ratio for your mid 30s and low 40s. At those levels, unless you are twinked, you just dont have the gear nor the HP pool to offset CoB's effect. Why? because the best lifetap top you have is Vampiric Embrance, the lvl 29 spell which is barely 220 hp recovery. That's highly sub-standarded at your 40s. <br /><br />Why is lvl 49 Lich such a performance boost you may ask? dont fool yourself, the secret of 49 Lich is not the Lich spell itself but rather the 49 spell Bond of Death. BoD is what makes 49 Lich feasible. Unfortunately, there is no CoB lifetap counterpart at your late 30's, early 40's.<br /><br />If it makes you feel better, I too used Allure over CoB for quite a number of levels myself. Be patient and dont let CoB bring you down. At level 49, everything changes for the better.<br /><br /><br /><br />Yag.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
