                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Pre-lich I kept CoB up continuously, and my gear was nothing to write home about.<br /><br />Usul summed up all points well, I would just add that you just have to get comfortable being very low health when pulling (40% at those levels is probably under 500 hp hehe, but I still pull sub-1000 at 63).<br /><br />Even bond of death at 49 is an extremely inefficient dot, and should only be cast when needed.  Vexing at 57 is a great upgrade but still relatively inefficient damage per mana-wise.<br /><br />Saryrn's Kiss at 62 is the first lifetap dot that approaches efficiency (~4 dpm is a very good ratio) and I'm much less careful about timing it to make sure it heals me just to full as it wears off.  It heals about 1500 hp with arch lich up, something for you to look forward to.<br /></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
